oux in Vienne, France, married Suzanne Rabouin in Batiscan, QC, in 1696."],"variants":[{"name":"Rocheleau","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Armand, Alphonse, Andre, Normand, Aurore, Cecile, Elphege, Emile, Fernand, Gilles, Mathieu.","Altered form of French <b>Rochereau</b>: topographic name from a diminutive of <i>rocher</i> ‘rock, crag, boulder’ (see   Rocher  ), or a habitational name from (Le) Rochereau, the name of several places in the western part of France. Compare   Rushlow  ."]},{"name":"Rochon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Andre, Aurele, Gaston, Michel, Yves, Adrien, Antoine, Fernande, Gaetan, Germain, Gilles.","Altered form of French <b>Rocheron</b>: topographic name from a diminutive of <i>rocher</i> ‘rock, crag, boulder’ (see   Rocher  ), or a habitational name from Le Rocheron, the name of two places in Indre-et-Loire.","French: diminutive of   Roche   ‘rock’."]},{"name":"Durocher","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Fernand, Gilles, Marcel, Normand, Alain, Antoine, Armand, Bibiane, Emile, Emilien, Gaetan.","French: topographic name from <i>rocher</i> ‘rock, crag, boulder’, with fused preposition and definite article <i>du</i> ‘from the’, denoting someone who lived in a rocky place; or a habitational name for someone from Le Rocher, the name of several places in various parts of France. Compare   Derusha   and   Rocher  .","Altered form of French   Desrochers  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"IV","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["probably a contracted form of  Jep , vernacular form of   Jacob   ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Nocher IV DE COLEMBERT was born in 1139, in France, his father, Josse II DE COLEMBERT, was 35 and his mother, Henriette DE RELY, was 21. He had at least 2 sons with Clothilde DE DESVRES. He died in 1198, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1139–1198":"1139–1198